text: Davaoeño (Dabawenyo) language is a native Mansakan language from the Davao Region of Mindanao, influenced by Cebuano and Tagalog. It is no longer spoken in Davao City, where speakers have shifted to a local dialect of Cebuano, known as Davaoeño Cebuano. ==Reference== Category:Austronesian languages Category:Languages of the Philippines
title: Davaoeño (language)
